comments.body: I see. Personally I don't think it's a good idea to report species from the wrong location. One of the purposes of iNat is to map the distribution of species and records like this sort of ruin that. It is very possible to report this species from the correct area without revealing the exact location. It's no secret that they occur on Mt Sibayak where I assume this individual was found.
Are the location of your records wrong? Seems to be very far down the mountain.
@ottob-c Location is not accurate. I put the location a bit away and then obscured to not give away the location, although I can see this one got quite close to Medan haha
